Purpose
This file implements the validator agent as an LLM-backed review stage.

Linear intent
1. Open `Lwt.Infix` so asynchronous result mapping stays linear.
2. Keep one local fallback size limit for deterministic validation.
3. Expose the agent id as `Validator`.
4. Provide local fallback validators for raw text and plan payloads.
5. Build a validator-specific LLM instruction that asks for a compact verdict, strengths, and risks.
6. Convert the LLM usage information into the framework metrics and notes format.
7. In `run`, accept `Text` payloads and ask the LLM for a compact validation report.
8. Fall back to the local text validator if the model returns no content.
9. In `run`, also accept `Plan` payloads so the validator can inspect planner output.
10. Fall back to the local plan validator if the model returns no content.
11. Return `Validation: ...` as a typed `Text` payload plus metrics and notes.
12. Reject unsupported payload kinds with a typed error payload.

